𝒥𝑜𝓊𝓇𝓃𝒶𝓁 𝟣𝟢 𝒥𝓊𝓁𝓎 𝟣𝟤, 𝟤𝟢𝟤𝟥

I feel like I’m inside a bubble. 

Work at 15, drop out of school at 16, side projects here and there, but this bubble… what is it? This bubble was a bit weird because even when I tried to ask questions, the chains around my ankles and wrists got tighter. Wait? Huh… I never noticed these chains. 
I mean this bubble can’t be bad right? My family are in one, my friends, my teachers, people all around me.
The older I got the more questions I asked myself. 
Why can I only move left to right? Why do I have to eat this food provided by the bubble? Why do I have to watch what the bubble puts on tv? Why do I have to follow the bubble rules? And I also noticed that the air kept getting harder to breathe as I get older, so I kept asking questions until something odd happened.

2 years ago I finally saw a crack on the bubble. I’m not going to lie it was a bit frightening but also weird because on this crack light came through. I’ve never seen this type of light in my life. I thought there was only one light which was inside the bubble already. But this light was gorgeous, it made me wonder what’s out there. More questions, more cracks, more light and I finally saw what was outside. It was endless possibilities, endless paths, dreams, fearlessness, courage, confidence, hope.
Now thinking back, I remember what happened 2 years ago.

I let go

workout
Lat pull-down - 3x10-12
. Grab a lat pulldown bar with an overhand grip outside of shoulder width and sit on the seat with your knees secured underneath the pads. 
. Begin with your arms extended overhead and your torso erect.
Leading with your elbows, pull the bar down until your upper arms reach at least parallel with the floor.
. Squeeze your shoulder blades together for a count at the bottom, then slowly return the bar to the start position.

Hammer strength machine row- 3x10-12
. Line yourself mid-chest with the pad, take a deep breath and brace your abs as you drive your chest into the pad.
. Squeezing your glutes, let the bar pull you forward slightly, giving you a nice additional stretch.
. From there, pull back each handle as you drive your chest into the pad, slightly creating a hinge into the movement. Squeeze your back, slow on the way back - repeat.

Db chest supported row - 3x10-12
. Let your arms hang straight down, palms facing each other. I like to feel a big stretch so I round my back while slightly letting my arms drop further down. 
. Drive your elbows toward the ceiling, bringing the dumbbells to your ribcage. Slowly reverse the move, and repeat.

The last two movements are basic bicep movements that are easy to do.

Rope bicep curl - 3x15

𝒥𝑜𝓊𝓇𝓃𝒶𝓁 𝟣𝟣 𝒮𝑒𝓅𝓉𝑒𝓂𝒷𝑒𝓇 𝟣𝟦, 𝟤𝟢𝟤𝟥

Don’t give it up

Belief is the strongest power we cannot explain or study but it’s real and powerful. You can use it to fuel you or you can leave it to harm you.
But that’s the beauty about such great power, it allows you to choose how you will use it.

A year ago I was sitting down thinking about how the heck am I going to pull this off. You’ve been working for 1 year on this project that is not guaranteed to work. But than I got to more thinking and asked myself who decides if this works or not? Well I cannot allowed others to decide if this works or not. If I was creating for others than I wouldn’t be creating from within, I’ll be creating from someones else’s heart and soul, and that’s nice but that wouldn’t be my creation.
At last I did find the answer and that was me.
I decide if this works or not. I have 100% control of it working or not. If I give up it doesn’t work, but if I keep going than I will make sure it works, I have belief in myself. 

Same can go for you in any field of your life.
Spark that little light of yours and see how it can change your approach towards whatever it is that you want to do.

Upper body & abs home workout!

One thing I used to teach my clients was the importance of training upper body. Many women hear these false claims about -
if you train upper body with weights you will become bulky like a man
- and that is not true. We can easily dispute this claim: the amount of the testosterone hormone is lower in women, especially in the upper limbs (most responsible for muscle growth) so this means naturally you will not gain like a man.

It is essential that the upper part is strengthened, to perform exercises such as squats, making the thighs and glutes receive a more intense workout. There’s many more benefits of training your upper body so don’t be scared and follow along with today’s workout!

Workout
Shoulder press - 15 reps
rest 30 sec
Front raise - 15 reps
rest 30 sec
Lateral raise - 15 reps
rest 30 sec
Plank dumbbell pass - 10 reps
rest 30 sec
Dumbbell sit tuck - 15 reps
Rest 90 sec

Do 3 rounds in total.

The truth is everyone gets tired but how you always still improve. Here’s my number one tip.

- Consistent breath work -

Breathing regulates your body and puts you in a control. On the other hand if your not being consistent with your breathing you will be stressing your body out instead. 

- Houston Methodist leading medicine on health article -
“When your breathing is regulated, your body and muscles receive the steady stream of oxygen it takes for them to operate most effectively,” says Dr. Hedt. “There’s also a calming effect to this. Consistent breathing can help trigger the parasympathetic nervous system, which essentially helps relax your body — allowing for better blood flow.”

So make sure to that you are not holding in your breath (happens to everyone) and find a breathing pattern that works well for you. The one I adapted is 2 quick inhales from the nose and 1 exhale from the mouth.
Have fun running ☀️

I’ve been in many dark places before and one thing that has allowed me to stay sane was movement. Running, gym, walking outside, etc.
It’s the one thing I go to when it’s bad. It’s my place of peace, my place of thought and my place of reflection. What a privilege it is to move.

I like my home and I like to stay inside haha but recently I’ve been taking walks and letting my mind wander. During my walk I was thinking about a conversation I had with my father. It was about the ego. We all have one, and most of us including myself make ego decisions and lead with it. It’s not a bad thing, ego can put us in higher positions, so we do need it but to loose control over it, that we cannot do.
“Learn to live with it rather than trying to make it disappear” my father said.

I believe ego is just the other side of who we are that can harm us if left alone or protect us if looked after. You know that side of you that is going straight forward and the other side who is walking away from it. What a beauty. It’s best most times to leave your ego out of it to be at peace with yourself. That said it is a part of us and that’s okay. But then again idk
random thoughts

Being alright with the thought and act of being alone is beautiful to me. I’m not saying leave everyone behind and be alone forever, of course not because I also do believe there’s power and beauty in interacting with one another.
For me the most beautiful part of being alone is that I am finally with the realest version of myself. The person who knows all your lies and truths is right there with you. The person who has hurt you and saved you most times is there with you. The person who knows what you do from the minute you wake up to the minute you go to sleep. You are there with a mind reader too haha. What a scary thought right? 
But that’s the beauty right there. You get to finally learn about this person. You get to ask this person the deepest questions you can think of about your life. What a beauty.

“No one saves us but ourselves. No one can and no one may. We ourselves must walk the path”

🇵🇪 we keep moving
